Rating: 0
I love that the lot of us aren't even following the recipe... I also used light coconut milk, 1 small onion instead of shallots, and 2 1/2 tsp red curry paste. I could have gone for even more, but the flavor was good and won my boyfriend's approval. Additionally, I added 1 1/2 cups peas and a dash of hot oil while he wasn't looking. First, I cooked the chicken in a wok until lightly browned and cooked through. I set it aside, added a bit more oil to the wok, and then added the onion and bell pepper. After these both showed slight browning, I added the curry paste and stirred well. This was followed by 1 1/2 cup peas, the coconut milk, and the fish sauce. I stirred it well, brought it to a boil, and then I let it simmer for a bit to thicken up. While it still had a little more to go, I added the chicken and let it thicken up a bit more. I'd already prepared Jasmine rice while I was doing the prep, so I was ready to roll. I threw on a little chopped basil and served with the lime slice on the side - yummy. I've had a few bland, soupy curries at Thai restaurants, so this was nice. Like I said though, I could've gone a little hotter.

